  "studyDescription": "The Stanford Heart Transplant Study tracked 103 patients who were accepted into the heart transplant program. Patients either received a transplant (treatment, n = 69) or did not (control, n = 34), based on donor heart availability. Survival status (alive or dead) was recorded at the end of the study. This is not a purely randomized experiment; treatment assignment depended on donor availability.",
